The paper discusses the development of an online environment for teaching Answer Set Programming to undergraduate and high school students. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories, as these are the areas where logic programming and Answer Set Programming are commonly studied. The paper also discusses the simplicity of the interface and the self-contained file system, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on teaching logic programming to students, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Education (cs.EDU) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the recent progress in logic programming, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category.
